88.1	Fermentation_(food)	Fermentation (food)	Fermentation in food processing typically is the conversion of carbohydrates to alcohols and carbon dioxide or organic acids using yeasts, bacteria, or a combination thereof, under anaerobic conditions. Fermentation in simple terms is the chemical conversion of sugars into ethanol. The science of fermentation is also known as zymology, or zymurgy.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/03/Wye_Valley_fermenter.jpg/300px-Wye_Valley_fermenter.jpg
